<Layout title="Projects" current={`/projects/`}>

<div class="page-header">
  <div class="eyebrow" data-en="// work & research" data-pl="// praca i badania">// work &amp; research</div>
  <h1 data-en="Projects"  data-pl="Projekty">Projects</h1>
  <p  data-en="Research collaborations, end-to-end ML systems, bioinformatics tools and experiments." data-pl="Współpraca badawcza, systemy ML end-to-end, narzędzia bioinformatyczne i eksperymenty.">Research collaborations, end-to-end ML systems, bioinformatics tools and experiments.</p>
</div>

<div class="proj-section-header">
  <span class="lbl" data-en="Research" data-pl="Badania">Research</span>
  <span class="sub">GMUM × Wawel Museum · Oct 2025 – Feb 2026</span>
  <div class="line"></div>
</div>

<div class="project-card">
  <div class="ph">
    <h3 data-en="2D → 3D Reconstruction — VistaDream + Depth Anything" data-pl="Rekonstrukcja 2D → 3D — VistaDream + Depth Anything">2D → 3D Reconstruction — VistaDream + Depth Anything</h3>
    <span class="proj-tag" data-type="research" data-en="research" data-pl="badania">research</span>
  </div>
  <p data-en="Integrated Depth Anything v2 into the VistaDream pipeline via a custom adapter. Modified depth normalization and camera logic for stable 3D projection from single 2D painting images. Generated 3D Gaussian Splatting (.ply) point clouds enabling interactive 3D exploration of museum artworks." data-pl="Zintegrowałem Depth Anything v2 z pipeline VistaDream przez własny adapter. Zmodyfikowałem normalizację głębi i logikę kamery dla stabilnej projekcji 3D z pojedynczych obrazów malarskich. Wygenerowano chmury punktów 3D Gaussian Splatting (.ply) umożliwiające interaktywną eksplorację dzieł muzealnych.">Integrated Depth Anything v2 into the VistaDream pipeline via a custom adapter. Modified depth normalization and camera logic for stable 3D projection from single 2D painting images. Generated 3D Gaussian Splatting (.ply) point clouds enabling interactive 3D exploration of museum artworks.</p>
  <div class="badge-row">
    <span class="badge">Python</span><span class="badge">Depth Anything v2</span>
    <span class="badge">VistaDream</span><span class="badge">3D Gaussian Splatting</span>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="project-card">
  <div class="ph">
    <h3 data-en="ML Digital Painting Restoration — Diffusion + LoRA + FLUX" data-pl="ML Restauracja Malarstwa — Diffusion + LoRA + FLUX">ML Digital Painting Restoration — Diffusion + LoRA + FLUX</h3>
    <span class="proj-tag" data-type="research" data-en="research" data-pl="badania">research</span>
  </div>
  <p data-en="Diffusion-based inpainting pipeline (FLUX.1-dev) for restoration of damaged historical artworks. Trained LoRA adapters for painter-specific style reconstruction. Improved stability via mask refinement and controlled inference tuning." data-pl="Pipeline inpaintingu oparty na dyfuzji (FLUX.1-dev) do restauracji uszkodzonych dzieł historycznych. Wytrenowano adaptery LoRA dla rekonstrukcji stylu konkretnych malarzy.">Diffusion-based inpainting pipeline (FLUX.1-dev) for restoration of damaged historical artworks. Trained LoRA adapters for painter-specific style reconstruction. Improved stability via mask refinement and controlled inference tuning.</p>
  <div class="badge-row">
    <span class="badge">Python</span><span class="badge">Diffusion models</span>
    <span class="badge">LoRA</span><span class="badge">FLUX.1-dev</span><span class="badge">inpainting</span>
  </div>
</div>




<div class="proj-section-header">
  <span class="lbl" data-en="Hackathon" data-pl="Hackathon">Hackathon</span>
  <span class="sub">EnsembleAI 2026 · Jagiellonian University</span>
  <div class="line"></div>
</div>

<div style="border: 1px solid var(--accent); border-radius: var(--r2); padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">

  <div style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 4px;">EnsembleAI Hackathon 2026</div>
  <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;"
       data-en="Multi-track ML competition · Jagiellonian University · 4 independent tasks"
       data-pl="Wielościeżkowy konkurs ML · Uniwersytet Jagielloński · 4 niezależne zadania">
    Multi-track ML competition · Jagiellonian University · 4 independent tasks
  </div>

  <div class="project-card">
    <div class="ph">
      <h3 data-en="Task 1 — ChEBI Ontology Prediction" data-pl="Zadanie 1 — Predykcja Ontologii ChEBI">Task 1 — ChEBI Ontology Prediction</h3>
      <span class="proj-tag" data-type="research" data-en="drug design" data-pl="projektowanie leków">drug design</span>
    </div>
    <p data-en="Hierarchical multi-label classification of small molecules into 500 ChEBI ontology classes. Used molecular fingerprints (ECFP, MACCS), GNNs and SMILES transformers. Classes form a DAG — child predictions must be consistent with parents. Metric: macro-averaged F1."
       data-pl="Hierarchiczna klasyfikacja wieloetykietowa cząsteczek do 500 klas ontologii ChEBI. Użyto odcisków molekularnych (ECFP, MACCS), GNN i transformerów SMILES. Klasy tworzą DAG — predykcje dzieci muszą być spójne z rodzicami. Metryka: makro F1.">
      Hierarchical multi-label classification of small molecules into 500 ChEBI ontology classes. Used molecular fingerprints (ECFP, MACCS), GNNs and SMILES transformers. Classes form a DAG — child predictions must be consistent with parents. Metric: macro-averaged F1.
    </p>
    <div class="badge-row">
      <span class="badge">GNN</span><span class="badge">RDKit</span><span class="badge">scikit-fingerprints</span><span class="badge">PyTorch Geometric</span><span class="badge">ChEBI</span><span class="badge">macro F1</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="project-card">
    <div class="ph">
      <h3 data-en="Task 2 — Context Retrieval for AI Coding (JetBrains)" data-pl="Zadanie 2 — Retrieval Kontekstu dla AI Coding (JetBrains)">Task 2 — Context Retrieval for AI Coding (JetBrains)</h3>
      <span class="proj-tag" data-type="research" data-en="LLM / RAG" data-pl="LLM / RAG">LLM / RAG</span>
    </div>
    <p data-en="Built a precision Context Collection Pipeline for Python codebases in collaboration with JetBrains Research. The pipeline retrieves the most relevant code snippets for a given developer query, used as context for LLM code completion. Evaluated via ChrF score across three models: Mellum, Codestral and Qwen2.5-Coder."
       data-pl="Pipeline do precyzyjnego zbierania kontekstu dla baz kodu Python we współpracy z JetBrains Research. System wyszukuje najtrafniejsze fragmenty kodu dla zapytania dewelopera, używane jako kontekst dla uzupełnień LLM. Oceniany przez ChrF na trzech modelach: Mellum, Codestral i Qwen2.5-Coder.">
      Built a precision Context Collection Pipeline for Python codebases in collaboration with JetBrains Research. The pipeline retrieves the most relevant code snippets for a given developer query, used as context for LLM code completion. Evaluated via ChrF score across three models: Mellum, Codestral and Qwen2.5-Coder.
    </p>
    <div class="badge-row">
      <span class="badge">RAG</span><span class="badge">LLM</span><span class="badge">JetBrains</span><span class="badge">FIM</span><span class="badge">ChrF</span><span class="badge">Python</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="project-card">
    <div class="ph">
      <h3 data-en="Task 3 — Heat Pump Grid Load Forecasting (Euros Energy)" data-pl="Zadanie 3 — Prognozowanie Obciążenia Sieci Pomp Ciepła (Euros Energy)">Task 3 — Heat Pump Grid Load Forecasting (Euros Energy)</h3>
      <span class="proj-tag" data-type="research" data-en="time-series" data-pl="szeregi czasowe">time-series</span>
    </div>
    <p data-en="Time-series extrapolation of electrical grid load for a network of heat pumps across Poland. Trained on 7 months of 5-minute telemetry (13 temperature sensors + geolocation metadata) to forecast per-device monthly load for May–October 2025. Extrapolation task: model must generalize to a new year. Metric: MAE."
       data-pl="Ekstrapolacja szeregów czasowych obciążenia sieci elektrycznej dla sieci pomp ciepła w Polsce. Trening na 7 miesiącach telemetrii 5-minutowej (13 czujników temperatury + metadane geolokalizacyjne) do prognozowania miesięcznego obciążenia per urządzenie na maj–październik 2025. Metryka: MAE.">
      Time-series extrapolation of electrical grid load for a network of heat pumps across Poland. Trained on 7 months of 5-minute telemetry (13 temperature sensors + geolocation metadata) to forecast per-device monthly load for May–October 2025. Extrapolation task: model must generalize to a new year. Metric: MAE.
    </p>
    <div class="badge-row">
      <span class="badge">time-series</span><span class="badge">XGBoost</span><span class="badge">feature engineering</span><span class="badge">MAE</span><span class="badge">Euros Energy</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="project-card" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
    <div class="ph">
      <h3 data-en="Task 4 — ECG Paper Digitization" data-pl="Zadanie 4 — Digitalizacja EKG z Papieru">Task 4 — ECG Paper Digitization</h3>
      <span class="proj-tag" data-type="flagship" data-en="medical" data-pl="medyczne">medical CV</span>
    </div>
    <p data-en="Computer vision pipeline converting scanned or photographed paper ECG printouts back into 1D digital time-series signals at 500 Hz. Handles real-world degradation: crumpled paper, handwritten annotations, B&W photocopies and poor lighting. Scored across three axes: signal morphology (Pearson correlation), amplitude calibration (SNR) and temporal alignment (cross-correlation)."
       data-pl="Pipeline Computer Vision konwertujący zeskanowane lub sfotografowane wydruki EKG z powrotem do cyfrowych sygnałów 1D (500 Hz). Obsługuje realne degradacje: pognieciony papier, notatki odręczne, kopie B&W i słabe oświetlenie. Ocena w trzech wymiarach: morfologia sygnału (korelacja Pearsona), kalibracja amplitudy (SNR) i wyrównanie czasowe (cross-correlation).">
      Computer vision pipeline converting scanned or photographed paper ECG printouts back into 1D digital time-series signals at 500 Hz. Handles real-world degradation: crumpled paper, handwritten annotations, B&W photocopies and poor lighting. Scored across three axes: signal morphology (Pearson correlation), amplitude calibration (SNR) and temporal alignment (cross-correlation).
    </p>
    <div class="badge-row">
      <span class="badge">Computer Vision</span><span class="badge">OpenCV</span><span class="badge">signal processing</span><span class="badge">NumPy</span><span class="badge">ECG</span><span class="badge">500 Hz</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>



